# ADR-001: Modular Monolith Architecture

Status: Accepted

Date: 2026-06-02

Decision Makers:
AgentForge Architecture Board

---

# Context

AgentForge is being developed as an enterprise-grade AI Agent Platform.

The platform must support:

- Coding Agents
- Data Science Agents
- Healthcare RCM Agents
- Transport Agents
- Future Domain Agents

The architecture must remain:

- Maintainable
- Extensible
- Observable
- Secure

A decision is required regarding the overall architectural style.

---

# Problem

Should AgentForge be built as:

Option A

Monolithic Application

---

Option B

Modular Monolith

---

Option C

Microservices

---

Option D

Distributed Service Platform

---

# Options Considered

## Option A — Traditional Monolith

Advantages

- Simple
- Fast development
- Easy deployment

Disadvantages

- Poor separation of concerns
- Difficult long-term scaling
- Architecture erosion risk

Decision

Rejected

---

## Option B — Modular Monolith

Advantages

- Strong module boundaries
- Easier development
- Easier testing
- Easier debugging
- Lower operational complexity
- Future extraction possible

Disadvantages

- Requires discipline
- Module boundaries must be enforced

Decision

Accepted

---

## Option C — Microservices

Advantages

- Independent scaling
- Independent deployment

Disadvantages

- Operational complexity
- Distributed transactions
- Higher infrastructure cost
- Premature for Version 1

Decision

Rejected

---

## Option D — Distributed Service Platform

Advantages

- Maximum flexibility

Disadvantages

- Extremely high complexity
- Unnecessary for current stage

Decision

Rejected

---

# Decision

AgentForge will be implemented as a Modular Monolith.

Repository Structure:

apps/
core/
domains/
infrastructure/
security/
agentops/
evaluation/
shared/

Modules must communicate through defined interfaces.

Direct coupling between modules is prohibited.

